The paper proposes a new algorithm for hypergraph bipartitioning, which is a problem in graph theory and combinatorial optimization. The algorithm is based on minimum S-T hyperedge cuts and maximum flows, which are concepts from network flow algorithms. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses the performance of the algorithm on various datasets and compares it to other hypergraph partitioners, which suggests that it belongs to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The paper uses numerical optimization techniques to optimize the balance and cut size of the bipartitions, which suggests that it belongs to cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). The paper also discusses the implementation details and computational complexity of the algorithm, which suggests that it belongs to cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Finally, the paper proposes a new algorithm that combines the proposed algorithm with an existing hypergraph partitioner, which suggests that it belongs to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
